íŸ@4cffde2406d664b697b16223872d2295aec2fed77dbff1cc57c5f0d4d56f0590⁄	Title: title: 'This week in Nushell #287'
Path: Highlights
Content:
With this week's TWiN, we start reporting on a few more repositories. That is, commits to almost

all
 
[link: https://github.com/nushell] Nushell repos
 will now be included in your curated weekly reading below.
Changes in recent nightlys and main include additional use of the new Custom Attributes feature to assign

a category to your custom commands. You 
did
 read about Custom Attributes in last week's TWiN, right?!
Also, @fdcred brought the latest Reedline into Nushell, so the new Vi-mode features you read about last week

are now available for dogfooding.
Last, but not least, thanks to @Kissaki for improving multiple codeblocks throughout the doc this week!
All commits in the most recent week:
íŸ@4f0fd856f59fe0542b796e540ce820c3b07ca60ac2fb45a229ee01af81495118⁄ÙTitle: title: 'This week in Nushell #287'
Path: Nushell
Content:
cosineblast 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15151] made 
``transpose``
 reject streams with non-record values
fdncred:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15148] bumped the Rust toolchain to 1.83.0
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15139] updated to the latest reedline
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15137] added 
``attr category``
 and 
``@category``
 to custom command attributes
ayax79:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15145] exposed a flag to not maintain order in 
``polars concat``
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15144] cleaned up minor Polars code
NotTheDr01ds:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15143] removed the BACKTRACE message for non-panic errors
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15130] removed inheritance for PROMPT variables in 
``default_env.nu``
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15129] replaced "function" with "command" in several user-facing docs
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15123] fixed a failing test for man version 2.13.0
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15122] added a 
``buffer_editor``
 example with arguments in 
``config nu --doc``
atahabaki 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15125] added zero padding for numeric ranges in Bracoxide
hongquan 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15057] added more directory autocomplete for 
``overlay use``
